              {
                  "class": "DepictionMarkdownView",
                  "markdown": "1) Automatically colorize badges' backgrounds and icons/folder labels based on app colors. If there are no notifications in a folder, it will color the label from the icons inside. For folders with multiple app notifications, it will color the folder badge with the highest notification count.\n\n2) Choose from 8 color schemes, including light, dark, chrome, and material that mimic pastel/blur types.\n\n3) Edit corner radius from square to circle.\n\n4) Add a border for badge backgrounds. The tweak features a smart algorithm that determines whether the border should be dark/light or something else based on your color scheme.\n\n5) Give your OCD a break with this tweak. Relax and enjoy your iOS experience!",
                  "useSpacing": true
